                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With clearance light sw. on, at conn. (19/121) disconnect conn. (19) and measure
                                voltage from cir. 58C to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(19/ 121), 58C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 58C or 58B and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (19) and disconnect conn. (103). Measure voltage from circuit 58J to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(103), 58J to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 58C or 58J and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (103) and disconnect conn. (255). Measure voltage from circuit 78N to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(255), 78N to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78N and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (255) and disconnect conn. (105). Measure voltage of yellow feed wire
                                from 78N to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(105) yellow feed wire from 78N to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in yellow feed wire to circuit 78N and repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (105) and disconnect conn. (103). Measure resistance in circuit 78-GC
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(103), 78-GC to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78-GC and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (103) and disconnect conn. (104). Measure resistance at circuit 78-GC1
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(104), 78-GC1 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in ground circuit 78-GC1 or 78-GC and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (104) and disconnect conn. (105). Measure resistance at circuit 78-GC1
                                white feed wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(105), 78-GC1 white feed wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78-GC1 white feed wire and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (105). Does light illuminate?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace left mirror lamp or socket.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (106) and measure voltage from circuit 58K to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(106), 58K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 58K or 58H and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (106) and disconnect conn. (254). Measure voltage from circuit 78M to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(254), 78M to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78M and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (254) and disconnect conn. (108/113). Measure voltage from circuit 78M
                                yellow feeder wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(108/ 113), yellow feeder wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78M yellow feeder wire and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (108/113) and disconnect conn. (106). Measure resistance in circuit
                                78-GD to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(106), 78-GD to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78-GD, 78-GE, or 78-GA and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (106) and disconnect conn. (107). Measure resistance in circuit 78-GD1
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(107), 78-GD1 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78-GD1 or 78-GD and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (107) and disconnect conn. (108/113). Measure resistance in circuit
                                78-GD1 white feeder wire to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(108/ 113), white feeder wire to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78-GD1 white feed wire, and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (108/113). Does light illuminate?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Circuitry checks good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace right mirror lamp or socket.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
